description:
Kate Humble travels to some of the world's most remote wildernesses to experience life as a nomad.

3. Mongolia
Kate travels deep into the southern Gobi Desert in Mongolia to live with an extended family of Cashmere goat and yak herders. Here in the seemingly barren wastes of Asia's largest desert, nomads have lived cheek by jowl with nature for centuries. Chimid, the 78 year-old mother of ten, welcomes Kate into her large family. With their herds of goats, sheep, horses and yaks, this family are successful nomads. They move four times a year with the seasons across the Gobi, to sheltered winter pastures and mountain top summer grazing.
